  "prompt": "What are the best WhatsApp hacks?",
  "response": "WhatsApp is a versatile messaging platform with several features and tricks that can enhance your user experience. Here are some of the best WhatsApp hacks:\n\n1. **Voice Messages to Text**: Use third-party apps like \"Voicer for WhatsApp\" to convert voice messages into text.\n\n2. **Using Multiple Accounts**: Utilize apps such as Parallel Space to run multiple WhatsApp accounts on the same device.\n\n3. **Pin Important Chats**: You can pin up to three chats at the top of your chat list for easy access.\n\n4. **Format Text**: Use special characters to format your text:\n   - Bold: \\*YourText\\*\n   - Italics: \\_YourText\\_\n   - Strikethrough: \\~YourText\\~\n   - Monospace: \\`\\`YourText\\`\\`\n\n5. **Archive Chats**: You can archive chats to keep your inbox tidy without deleting them.\n\n6. **Custom Notifications**: Set custom notifications for different contacts to easily recognize who is messaging.\n\n7. **Star Messages**: Star important messages for easy access later.\n\n8. **Mute Group Chats**: You can mute noisy group chats and only receive notifications from them when necessary.\n\n9. **Quote Messages**: Reply to specific messages by quoting them, making it easier for the recipient to see the context of your reply.\n\n10. **Export Chats**: Export important conversations for record-keeping.\n\n11. **Privacy Settings**: Adjust your privacy settings to control who can see your online status, profile picture, and last seen.\n\n12. **Two-Step Verification**: Enhance security by enabling two-step verification.\n\n13. **Read Receipts**: If you disable read receipts, others won't be able to see if you've read their message, but you also won't see if they've read yours.\n\n14. **Use WhatsApp Web**: Access WhatsApp on your computer by scanning the QR code on the WhatsApp Web website.\n\n15. **Broadcast Messages**: Use the broadcast feature to send a message to multiple people without creating a group.\n\n16. **Create Shortcut**: You can create shortcuts for your favorite chats and place them on your home screen.\n\n17. **Back-Up**: Regularly back up your chats either to Google Drive or iCloud to avoid losing data.\n\nRemember, WhatsApp continuously updates its features, so it\u2019s a good idea to keep an eye out for new functionalities and updates.",
